The article is a transcript of President Biden's remarks at Minneapolis-Saint Paul International Airport. In the conversation, President Biden expresses his desire for the Build Back Better plan to pass as soon as possible. He also mentions that he will be discussing new vaccine requirements on Thursday. When asked about visiting Michigan to talk to families affected by a recent incident, the President states that he doesn't have the details and is unsure if he will be able to go. Regarding travel restrictions on countries in Southern Africa, President Biden says that it will depend on the evolving situation and that he is committed to coordinating with Allies unlike his predecessor, President Trump.